commentBody:
@Kate Tani

You're not the only one.  I ignored all the obvious difficulties up until the final grind.  I was sure it was right.

Not quite double my Sat avg so that wasn't my only problem.

@Barry Ancona
@Kate Tani

My mind kept coming back to WADI, but I wasn't sure it was even a word.  

Comforting to now read that others were slowed by that one.

@Barry Ancona

That’s what I get for commenting without reading the previous comments. (Hey, it was past my bedtime!)

I egotistically assumed that I would be one of the few people who put WAdi before WASH. I misunderestimated my fellow solvers (apologies for that).

@Eric Hougland
I stuck with WAdi through three passes before I even considered if there was an English equivalent. Too much reading of Middle Eastern history and literature.
Now I have another entry for my KeaLoa list.

@Whoa Nellie

I sometimes wonder if I would be more favorably disposed to Bolero if I didn’t associate it so strongly with the movie 10 (which I really disliked back in 1979). 

I really wanted “monotonous” to fit at 17A.

@Whoa Nellie,

And I was thinking of Bo Derek. 

Not necessarily trying to keep her out of my mind’s eye, though.

@Alan Young

Totes legit. 

I lost a lot of time to the same mistake.

@Steve L

I'm honestly and naively a bit shocked that anyone using XWStats would use "aids" of any kind.  What the devil is the point of comparing times to other people's if you're already ch__ting?

Weird.  At least I agree with the rating today.

@mlw
This was my longest solve in months, I think. (I don't really keep track.) 
And it _felt_ slow. I mean really slow. Like 'multiple passes without adding a single piece of fill' slow. I filled in the bottom half s-l-o-w-l-y, only to look at the top half and realize I had a bunch of nonsense crosses to figure out. Which I did with pass after pass after pass...

@Rachel118

Saturday puzzles are supposed to be very hard. 

Every single week.

@Dave K.
"the answers to the clues were too vague or could've been a dozen other answers."

This is what Saturday puzzles are supposed to be like. This is what they WERE like, before the editors nerfed them to appease people who are terrified of a challenge.

@Jill

Now you've got me thinking about "bones" in the G-SPOT.

I might try to Google it, but I'm pretty sure I know what I'd find.

@Roberta

Right on.

I'm usually all over a nit like a cheap suit, but I missed this one.

@Stephen

Yes.  Both kanJI and WAdi led me astray.

Oh, and letIn instead of ADMIT.

@Stephen,

Kanji was my first thought, too. Without looking it up, I’m not sure that it doesn’t mean what the clue said. 

EMOJI made sense to me when I thought of it.

@Al  in Pittsburgh
(raises hand for letIn)
(and again wishes for a serif)

@SP

I was sure it had to be kanji - emoji seemed too easy - and I held on to it for a while.

Thanks for the shout-out.

@SP
This was the first time I’ve ever truly given up, it was after 15 minutes and I was really glad I did when I saw the answers. It would have been excruciating looking at this for 60-90 mins, which around what I usually give to a Fri/Sat/Sun.

It was the first time I’ve ever Revealed puzzle and now I have an incredibly unrealistic best time for a Saturday.

@Becky

